link rel=\"alternate\" media=\"only screen and (max-width: 720px)\" href=\"//en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thalassius_of_Syria\"/>\n<link rel=\"alternate\" type=\"application/x-wiki\" title=\"Edit this page\" href=\"/w/index.php?title=Thalassius_of_Syria&amp;action=edit\"/>\n<link rel=\"edit\" title=\"Edit this page\" href=\"/w/index.php?title=Thalassius_of_Syria&amp;action=edit\"/>\n<link rel=\"apple-touch-icon\" href=\"/static/apple-touch/wikipedia.png\"/>\n<link rel=\"shortcut icon\" href=\"/static/favicon/wikipedia.ico\"/>\n<link rel=\"search\" type=\"application/opensearchdescription+xml\" href=\"/w/opensearch_desc.php\" title=\"Wikipedia (en)\"/>\n<link rel=\"EditURI\" type=\"application/rsd+xml\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd\"/>\n<link rel=\"license\" href=\"//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/\"/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thalassius_of_Syria\"/>\n<link rel=\"dns-prefetch\" href=\"//login.wikimedia.org\"/>\n<link rel=\"dns-prefetch\" href=\"//meta.wikimedia.org\" />\n</head>\n<body class=\"mediawiki ltr sitedir-ltr mw-hide-empty-elt ns-0 ns-subject mw-editable page-Thalassius_of_Syria rootpage-Thalassius_of_Syria skin-vector action-view skin-vector-legacy\"><div id=\"mw-page-base\" class=\"noprint\"></div>\n<div id=\"mw-head-base\" class=\"noprint\"></div>\n<div id=\"content\" class=\"mw-body\" role=\"main\">\n\t<a id=\"top\"></a>\n\t<div id=\"siteNotice\" class=\"mw-body-content\"><!-- CentralNotice --></div>\n\t<div class=\"mw-indicators mw-body-content\">\n\t</div>\n\t<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\" lang=\"en\">Thalassius of Syria</h1>\n\t<div id=\"bodyContent\" class=\"mw-body-content\">\n\t\t<div id=\"siteSub\" class=\"noprint\">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>\n\t\t<div id=\"contentSub\"></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"contentSub2\"></div>\n\t\t\n\t\t<div id=\"jump-to-nav\"></div>\n\t\t<a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#mw-head\">Jump to navigation</a>\n\t\t<a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#searchInput\">Jump to search</a>\n\t\t<div id=\"mw-content-text\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\" class=\"mw-content-ltr\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Saint Thalassius of Syria</b> undertook the call of <a href=\"/wiki/Trinity\" title=\"Trinity\">God</a> to life as a <a href=\"/wiki/Hermit\" title=\"Hermit\">hermit</a> in the fifth century.\n</p><p>Thalassius is recorded to have entered into solitude at a young age near a village named Targala in <a href=\"/wiki/Byzantine_Syria\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Byzantine Syria\">Byzantine Syria</a>.  He is said to have dwelt there living the <a href=\"/wiki/Ascetic\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ascetic\">ascetic</a> life with no shelter for nearly forty years.\n</p><p>Thalassius' was a <a href=\"/wiki/Soul\" title=\"Soul\">soul</a> filled with humbleness, simplicity, and a gentle nature.  God manifested in the <a href=\"/wiki/Saint\" title=\"Saint\">saint</a> the gifts of powerful <a href=\"/wiki/Intercession\" title=\"Intercession\">intercession</a> and healing for which he gained considerable renown.\n</p><p>In time many came to join Thalassius in the <a href=\"/wiki/Hermit\" title=\"Hermit\">eremitic life</a> and he welcomed them as he would welcome <a href=\"/wiki/Christ\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Christ\">Christ</a>, building them <a href=\"/wiki/Skete\" title=\"Skete\">cells</a> with his own hands.\n</p><p>Saint Thalassius, Hermit of Syria is said to have died peacefully and is commemorated 22 February by the <a href=\"/wiki/Eastern_Orthodox\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Eastern Orthodox\">Eastern Orthodox</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Byzantine_Catholic\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Byzantine Catholic\">Byzantine Catholic</a> Churches.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Thalassius_of_Syria&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r936637989\">.mw-parser-output .portal{border:solid #aaa 1px;padding:0}.mw-parser-output .portal.tleft{margin:0.5em 1em 0.5em 0}.mw-parser-output .portal.tright{margin:0.5em 0 0.5em 1em}.mw-parser-output .portal>ul{display:table;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0.1em;max-width:175px;background:#f9f9f9;font-size:85%;line-height:110%;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold}.mw-parser-output .portal>ul>li{display:table-row}.mw-parser-output .portal>ul>li>span:first-child{display:table-cell;padding:0.2em;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center}.mw-parser-output .portal>ul>li>span:last-child{display:table-cell;padding:0.2em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em;vertical-align:middle}</style><div role=\"navigation\" aria-label=\"Portals\" class=\"noprint portal plainlist tright\">\n<ul>\n<li><span><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/Gloriole_blur.svg/32px-Gloriole_blur.svg.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"32\" height=\"28\" class=\"noviewer\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/Gloriole_blur.svg/48px-Gloriole_blur.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/Gloriole_blur.svg/64px-Gloriole_blur.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"32\" data-file-height=\"28\" /></span><span><a href=\"/wiki/Portal:Saints\" title=\"Portal:Saints\">Saints portal</a></span></li></ul></div>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Christian_monasticism\" title=\"Christian monasticism\">Christian monasticism</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Stylites\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Stylites\">Stylites</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Poustinia\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Poustinia\">Poustinia</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Thalassius_of_Syria&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Reference